text=:Category: LinguisticDiscriminationInTheWild%0a:Essential: {Category.LinguisticDiscriminationInTheWild$:essential}%0a:Title: Linguistic Discrimination against "aight" in BVE%0a:Author: nithyas%0a:Section: D%0a:Completed: 23.04.2021 - 20:46%0a:Status: complete%0a%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradeitem:)%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradingcomment:)%0a%0a----%0a%0a%0a%25blue%25 '''Grading History'''%0a%0a[[#history]]%0a#foxbegin 210505-020742-51800#%0a* [-04.05.2021 - 19:07-] || TA_lili marked as complete%0a#foxend 210505-020742-51800#%0a[[#historyend]]%0a%0a%25blue%25 '''Comments for student'''%0a%0a[[#comments]]%0a%0a[[#commentsend]]%0a%0a----%0a----%0a!!%0a%0aSummary: \\%0a%0a[[#summary]]%0a%0aOne PhD Quora user suggests "aight" is not a real word%0a%0a[[#summaryends]]%0a%0a----%0a[[#content]]%0a%0aBlack Vernacular English is often the target of linguistic discrimination and is perceived as a dialect spoken by the uneducated. Many believe that BVE “sounds less intelligent” and is just an improperly spoken version of Standard American English. Various words and phrases in BVE have been criticized for being ungrammatical. One example of a word from this dialect is “aight”, which has transcription [ˈaˌɐɪt], and this Quora user, who actually has a PhD in English, claims that “aight” is not a real word and does not meet the standards to be considered a real word. %0a%0aThe original transcription of the word is [ɔːlˈɹaɪt]. As we can see, there is the medial consonant deletion (of [l] and [ɹ]) as well as the diphthongization of the first vowel in the sentence (the length of the vowel sound is extended and is characterized by two different vowel sounds put together). Finally, the change from /ɔ/ to /a/ and /ɐ/ also involves a change in the backness of the vowel. Namely, the “ungrammatical” version changes the first vowel in the word to be more to the front than the vowel in the conventional pronunciation. Thus, the criticisms of the use of “aight” instead of “alright” are criticisms of the above phenomena.  %0a%0aLink to example: https://www.quora.com/Do-you-consider-aight-to-be-a-word %0a%0a%0a[[#contentends]]%0a----%0a(:GradedBy: TA_lili:)
